description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a self-motivated and driven individual to join our expanding team on a secondment basis for 12 months to cover maternity leave. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The successful candidate will be an integral part of the team, working closely to support the Lead Infection Prevention Control Specialist in the delivery of a high quality service, and to support the Trust in meeting the requirements of the Health and Social Care Act 2008: code of practice on the prevention and control of infections. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; You will be working as a member of an award winning, friendly, supportive specialised Infection Prevention and Control team and your role will include assisting in the citywide delivery of the infection prevention and control strategy which includes; taking a specific lead on HCAI&#39;S, surveillance and investigation of health care associated infections. You will support the delivery of educating and training staff in infection control practices, auditing, innovative preventative measures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will also be the opportunity to carry out other specific IP&amp;C projects such as the reduction in gram negative blood stream infections. We work citywide supporting LCH staff, patients and services, as well as services throughout the wider system such as schools and nurseries, GP Practices, Care Homes etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant requires the ability to make decisions, work well within a team in a fast paced environment and the ability to work independently when required is essential. You will have a qualification in Infection Prevention and Control. You will have excellent communication skills, be able to work flexibly and be committed to meeting deadlines and targets. You must display a passion for high quality patient focused care. You should have suitable experience of working within the field of Infection Prevention and Control and have experience of supporting change management. A positive, flexible approach is paramount and you must be effective at motivating and influencing staff at all levels. Excellent leadership, communication and interpersonal skills are essential to this role. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The post will be based at Chapeltown Health Centre, however post holders will be expected to work throughout the city as required, therefore being a car driver is essential. Due to the expansion of the team there will be an option to work agile.&lt;/p&gt;
